One of the Yaaukanigas, a man advanced in years, came with his family to be baptized at the very beginning of the colony. The strict integrity of this excellent man ob- tained him the name of Jz'can Bueno, and his wife, daughter, and female Negro captive were equally exemplary in their conduct.
